  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 604b577af8a43c942bd5251f25245dcd, type: 3}
  m_Name: DroneShooter_Lore
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GV.UI.ShipLoreData
  shipName: Drone Shooter
  tagline: No pilot. No mercy. No one hears you call for backup.
  rarity: Uncommon
  shipClass: Autonomous Strike Drone
  originLabel: Developed In
  originName: Inkara - INTARi Intelligence Network
  factionLabel: Operators
  factionName: INTARi Remote Corps
  powerSystem: Compact Fission Cell Array
  combatRole: Expendable rapid-response hunter
  specialAbility: "Swarm Protocol - splits into three smaller sub-drones that attack
    from different angles simultaneously. Each sub-drone carries reduced firepower
    but independent targeting. Recombines after eight seconds or if any sub-drone is
    destroyed."
  backstory: "The Drone Shooter began as an INTARi surveillance platform. Inkara's
    intelligence network needed eyes everywhere - over Daitya Giri's volcanic forges,
    above Nandana's royal shipyards, inside the storm corridors around Garuda Vana.
    The original drones were small, silent, and completely unarmed. Then the Atom Riders
    started shooting them down. Saharai's desert raiders figured out how to jam their
    signals. Elgorn Fall's ERGOVAn patrols deployed net launchers that snagged them
    mid-flight. The INTARi response was predictable - if the drones keep getting destroyed,
    make them shoot back. The first armed variant was crude. A compact fission cell
    bolted to a reinforced surveillance frame with a single forward-mounted cannon.
    It worked better than anyone expected. The drones were fast, cheap, and disposable.
    Where a Spaceship costs a small fortune in Nuclear-P fuel cells and a Vimana is
    literally irreplaceable, a Drone Shooter can be manufactured in three days from
    standard industrial components. Inkara built hundreds. The INTARi Remote Corps
    operates them from hidden bunkers scattered across all nine Countries. No pilot
    sits inside. No one risks their life. The drone flies, fights, and if it gets
    destroyed, another one rolls off the assembly line. The Kingdoms consider them
    cowardly. The Atom Riders consider them unreliable. The INTARi consider them the
    future of warfare."
  strengths: "Mass-produced and expendable - losses are replaceable within days\nNo
    pilot means no risk to human or Sarathi life\nSmall profile makes it difficult
    to target compared to full-size vessels\nSwarm Protocol overwhelms single targets
    with coordinated multi-angle attacks"
  weaknesses: "Minimal armor - a single clean hit from an Astra weapon or Nuclear-P
    cannon will destroy it\nCompact fission cells provide limited sustained firepower
    compared to full reactors\nRemote signal link can be jammed or intercepted by
    advanced electronic warfare\nNo Thara Resonance and no onboard pilot means zero
    adaptability to unexpected combat situations"
  history: "INTARi deploys first unarmed surveillance drones across all nine Countries
    and Kingdoms\nAtom Riders and ERGOVAn patrols begin systematically destroying
    surveillance drones\nSaharai desert raiders develop signal jamming technology
    targeting drone control frequencies\nINTARi engineers in Inkara arm the first
    combat variant with a compact fission cannon\nMass production begins - Inkara's
    factories produce hundreds of armed drones\nINTARi Remote Corps established as
    a dedicated drone warfare division\nFirst Swarm Protocol test destroys a stolen
    Vimana hull in under twelve seconds\nKingdoms and Countries both attempt to ban
    autonomous weapons - INTARi ignores both"
